![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/23643a8e-cb88-441e-849f-b1652237dfdd/10719.jpg)

“The two day one guys. The main character, and the main antagonist.”

MJF tells Hangman he's happy to antagonize him into losing the World Championship in his first defense. Hangman laughs and tells him he's talking as if he actually has a title shot upcoming.

Hangman will never GIVE MJF a title shot. MJF will have to look Hangman in the eye and declare he's using his Casino Gauntlet opportunity.

MJF still has an issue with the way the crowd treats Hangman as if he's perfect or their god. When MJF was a young man, he learned that if God is all knowing and all powerful then clearly he can't be good.

Neither is Hangman. MJF IS going to show the world that Hangman is no god. Hangman is a weak-minded, depressed alcoholic child. MJF would rather be looked at as the devil than a false idol.

MJF does not just want the championship. He wants to lift the sheet from the eyes of the fans to expose Hangman for a fake god. MJF wants to CRUCIFY Hangman.

Hangman says MJF keeps talking as if he has a shot at the title. He doesn't. He has a contract he can cash in but he WON'T because he's a coward.

# **MJF IS NO COWARDS. MJF HAS EXECUTED HIS CONTRACT IN THE HEAT OF THE MOMENT.**

He realized what he's done. Hangman just goaded MJF into using his contract at Forbidden Door

